for myself

504
00:22:08.941 --> 00:22:10.072
in St. Louis...

505
00:22:10.392 --> 00:22:12.208
<i>That</i> was to be my destiny.

506
00:22:14.235 --> 00:22:16.000
And now I know I was right.

507
00:22:16.838 --> 00:22:18.820
Only it turns out the saint
is not a city.

508
00:22:18.845 --> 00:22:20.583
but a handsome man.

509
00:22:20.608 --> 00:22:21.821
with a most...

510
00:22:22.064 --> 00:22:23.923
<i>agreeable disposition.</i>

511
00:22:24.375 --> 00:22:26.292
You're his destiny.
Louis.

512
00:22:27.328 --> 00:22:29.042
Destined to be
very good friends.

513
00:22:31.417 --> 00:22:34.500
The Orient room is available
for the next few hours. Miss Lily.

514
00:22:34.921 --> 00:22:38.042
The gentlemen are swappin'
andouille sausage recipes. Miss Carroll.

515
00:22:38.500 --> 00:22:39.208
Hmm.

516
00:22:55.757 --> 00:22:57.299
The Orient room
is yours. monsieur.

517
00:22:57.819 --> 00:22:59.875
Please get my friend here
anything he wants.

518
00:23:00.246 --> 00:23:01.459
Wonderful to meet you.

519
00:23:01.631 --> 00:23:03.750
I do hope I run into
you again. Louis.

520
00:23:05.260 --> 00:23:06.870
<i>Emasculation</i>

521
00:23:06.894 --> 00:23:08.476
<i>and admiration</i>

522
00:23:08.501 --> 00:23:09.999
<i>in equal measure.</i>

523
00:23:11.054 --> 00:23:12.784
I wanted to murder the man.

524
00:23:13.994 --> 00:23:15.625
and I wanted to <i>be</i> the man.

525
00:23:20.358 --> 00:23:22.250
I had come there for Lily.

526
00:23:23.292 --> 00:23:25.500
But I left thinking of only him.

527
00:24:05.677 --> 00:24:06.458
Come now.

528
00:24:10.116 --> 00:24:11.417
Who the devil...

529
00:24:26.750 --> 00:24:29.167
Our friends in the police tell me
there's an outbreak of fever in town.

530
00:24:30.328 --> 00:24:32.500
It's unfortunates
living near the wharf. mostly.

531
00:24:32.946 --> 00:24:34.726
If you find yourself
riverside of Decatur...

532
00:24:34.751 --> 00:24:36.875
... you have only<i>yourself</i>
to blame. I say.

533
00:24:37.243 --> 00:24:38.042
Agreed.

534
00:24:38.704 --> 00:24:40.308
Still. very peculiar.
they say.

535
00:24:40.587 --> 00:24:41.801
Each one the same --

536
00:24:41.930 --> 00:24:43.392
small wounds to the body.

537
00:24:43.657 --> 00:24:46.875
and upon examination.
entirely devoid of blood.

538
00:24:47.806 --> 00:24:49.797
It is their theory
some new kind of rat

539
00:24:49.889 --> 00:24:50.792
has come ashore.

540
00:24:51.157 --> 00:24:52.833
Of the six foot variety.

541
00:24:53.883 --> 00:24:56.208
We call those <i>bureaucrats</i>
in France.

542
00:24:59.204 --> 00:25:00.083
Gentlemen.

543
00:25:00.243 --> 00:25:02.375
well. you all know
Louis du Lac.

544
00:25:03.540 --> 00:25:07.167
Louis. let me introduce
you to Mr. Lestat de Lioncourt.

545
00:25:07.321 --> 00:25:09.125
We met already.
Mr. Anderson. sir.

546
00:25:09.241 --> 00:25:11.083
In front of a florist.
wasn't it?

547
00:25:11.591 --> 00:25:13.834
We both wanted
the last bouquet of lilies...

548
00:25:16.458 --> 00:25:18.625
Aren't you gonna ask the
Alderman how his head is. Louis?

549
00:25:19.042 --> 00:25:21.084
Now. why would I do that.
Mr. Anderson. sir?

550
00:25:22.583 --> 00:25:24.541
You see. Mr. Fenwick.
just as I told you.

551
00:25:24.857 --> 00:25:26.500
a most discreet Negro.

552
00:25:26.693 --> 00:25:29.458
Would that his doctor
had the same standards.

553
00:25:29.929 --> 00:25:31.625
Gentlemen.
show your cards.

554
00:25:34.634 --> 00:25:35.809
Hoo!

555
00:25:36.196 --> 00:25:37.044
Mr. Lioncourt.

556
00:25:37.069 --> 00:25:37.880
your hand

557
00:25:38.055 --> 00:25:39.875
is incomprehensible.

558
00:25:40.704 --> 00:25:41.583
Oh. yes.

559
00:25:42.759 --> 00:25:44.125
I'm terrible at cards.

560
00:25:44.243 --> 00:25:45.875
Did I not mention
that to everyone?

561
00:25:46.478 --> 00:25:50.308
Would you mind getting me
some more of these "money chips"?

562
00:25:53.250 --> 00:25:53.958
Louis.

563
00:25:54.171 --> 00:25:57.765
did you know that Alderman Fenwick here
recently purchased both the title and deed

564
00:25:57.790 --> 00:25:59.542
to the Horton rooming house
on Villere Street?

565
00:25:59.659 --> 00:26:01.360
Yeah. Mr. Anderson believes
it could make

566
00:26:01.460 --> 00:26:02.833
a fine sportin' house.

567
00:26:02.962 --> 00:26:05.875
I recommended the Alderman
find a managing partner

568
00:26:06.164 --> 00:26:07.421
before he commits his money.

569
00:26:07.499 --> 00:26:09.917
I recommended he
think of you. Louis.

570
00:26:09.942 --> 00:26:12.167
Very kind of you.
Mr. Anderson. sir.

571
00:26:12.471 --> 00:26:14.000
What do you think
of the location?

572
00:26:15.125 --> 00:26:16.834
It ain't Basin Street.

573
00:26:17.176 --> 00:26:19.625
But throw enough
Edison bulbs on the façade.

574
00:26:19.685 --> 00:26:21.250
get a good margin
on the alcohol.

575
00:26:21.280 --> 00:26:23.667
no-nonsense Madam
to keep the girls clean.

576
00:26:23.789 --> 00:26:25.725
I reckon a man
could make a decent sum.

577
00:26:25.750 --> 00:26:27.267
Yes. sir.
Mr. Fenwick. sir.

578
00:26:27.458 --> 00:26:29.375
I said you'd do it for 10 percent.

579
00:26:30.958 --> 00:26:32.517
A - all respects.
Mr. Anderson.

580
00:26:33.047 --> 00:26:35.250
but you proposing 10 percent
for all the work?

581
00:26:35.875 --> 00:26:36.667
Fifteen?

582
00:26:38.208 --> 00:26:39.750
There's capital
investment.

583
00:26:40.750 --> 00:26:42.000
and there's labour.

584
00:26:43.208 --> 00:26:45.142
Both has its seat
at the table.

585
00:26:45.260 --> 00:26:47.125
Wouldn't you say.
Mr. Lestat?

586
00:26:49.292 --> 00:26:51.517
Well. I can only speak
of my experience.

587
00:26:51.773 --> 00:26:54.017
which is. I'm sure.
different in my country.

588
00:26:54.125 --> 00:26:56.663
<i>Par exemple</i>. you fine gentlemen
have heard of the success story

589
00:26:56.688 --> 00:26:57.917
that is <i>Le Bon Marché.</i>

590
00:26:57.942 --> 00:27:00.102
shopping experience
like no other.

591
00:27:01.656 --> 00:27:02.468
Aristide Boucicaut invests
in a new vision...

592
00:27:01.487 --> 00:27:03.125
<i>- These men look down on you.</i>

593
00:27:03.684 --> 00:27:04.718
<i>I have to say. </i>

594
00:27:04.758 --> 00:27:07.225
<i>I find it appalling
how men like yourself</i>

595
00:27:07.250 --> 00:27:09.142
<i>are treated in
this country of yours.</i>

596
00:27:09.390 --> 00:27:11.939
It is undeniable.
I came to my wealth honestly

597
00:27:11.964 --> 00:27:13.850
and at great sacrifice.
I might add.

598
00:27:13.875 --> 00:27:16.183
However. it was not
the sacrifice of many.

599
00:27:16.208 --> 00:27:18.125
I had no partners
in my various...

600
00:27:17.898 --> 00:27:19.166
<i>- 10 percent.</i>

601
00:27:19.806 --> 00:27:21.417
<i>- 15 percent.</i>

602
00:27:19.278 --> 00:27:20.552
The financial risks...

603
00:27:25.042 --> 00:27:26.709
<i>Do you not know your value?</i>

604
00:27:31.638 --> 00:27:33.306
<i>Do you suffer these indignities</i>

605
00:27:33.330 --> 00:27:33.907
<i>for some...</i>

606
00:27:33.932 --> 00:27:35.334
... <i>larger purpose?</i>

607
00:27:43.208 --> 00:27:45.833
<i>And do you think two pair
will win the hour?</i>

608
00:27:52.067 --> 00:27:55.501
I believe there is great
opportunity in this city.

609
00:27:55.846 --> 00:27:56.384
but. 

610
00:27:56.481 --> 00:27:57.542
to seize it. 

611
00:27:57.943 --> 00:28:00.250
I'll need protection
from the wolves.

612
00:28:15.208 --> 00:28:16.208
And that's all to say.

613
00:28:16.295 --> 00:28:18.417
forgive me. Mr.
de Pointe du Lac. for my bias.

614
00:28:18.442 --> 00:28:20.653
but where is the business
if there is no capital?

615
00:28:20.678 --> 00:28:21.888
It does not exist. No?

616
00:28:22.455 --> 00:28:23.458
Alright. boys.
Show 'em.

617
00:28:27.760 --> 00:28:29.042
Ooh.

618
00:28:29.635 --> 00:28:30.764
Full boat.

619
00:28:30.788 --> 00:28:31.959
Mr. du Lac...

620
00:28:33.440 --> 00:28:34.776
Got you beat. Tom.

621
00:28:35.260 --> 00:28:36.917
<i>He wouldn't tell me
how he did it.</i>

622
00:28:37.417 --> 00:28:39.625
<i>his trick to make
the world stop.</i>

623
00:28:40.292 --> 00:28:41.764
<i>"In time. Louis.</i>

624
00:28:41.788 --> 00:28:42.821
<i>Patience. Louis.</i>

625
00:28:42.846 --> 00:28:44.833
<i>Ask me next week. Louis."</i>

626
00:28:45.208 --> 00:28:46.447
<i>You started hanging out?</i>

627
00:28:46.955 --> 00:28:48.183
<i>He was in love
with my city</i>

628
00:28:48.417 --> 00:28:50.209
<i>and wanted to know
everything he could about it.</i>

629
00:28:51.034 --> 00:28:54.334
<i>So you played</i> docent
<i>to the gentleman vampire?</i>

630
00:28:54.458 --> 00:28:57.541
<i>He had not revealed
his vampire nature yet.</i>

631
00:28:57.932 --> 00:28:59.667
I'm assuming you
only met at night.

632
00:29:00.026 --> 00:29:01.292
It's New Orleans.

633
00:29:01.379 --> 00:29:04.333
<i>Days</i> are for sleeping off
the previous evening's damage.

634
00:29:04.625 --> 00:29:06.486
Perfect cover
for a vampire.

635
00:29:06.542 --> 00:29:08.792
Racing ahead <i>again</i>.
Mr. Molloy.

636
00:29:09.010 --> 00:29:11.375
<i>Let the tale seduce you.</i>

637
00:29:12.693 --> 00:29:15.096
Just as I was seduced...

638
00:29:16.417 --> 00:29:18.892
<i>Money would arrive.
wired from France.</i>

639
00:29:18.917 --> 00:29:21.725
<i>and the shopkeepers. who would
usually close at sunset.</i>

640
00:29:21.750 --> 00:29:23.875
<i>were very happy
to accommodate him.</i>

641
00:29:24.651 --> 00:29:28.318
<i>He ransacked the import houses
to furnish his townhouse.</i>

642
00:29:28.625 --> 00:29:31.149
<i>ravaged the booksellers of
their oldest volumes</i>

643
00:29:31.174 --> 00:29:32.416
<i>for a library.</i>

644
00:29:32.705 --> 00:29:33.326
<i>And.</i>

645
00:29:33.350 --> 00:29:34.967
<i>with encouragement.</i>

646
00:29:35.542 --> 00:29:36.850
<i>updated his wardrobe</i>

647
00:29:36.875 --> 00:29:38.917
<i>to the fashion trends
of the season.</i>

648
00:29:39.729 --> 00:29:41.858
<i>It was a cold winter that year.</i>

649
00:29:42.275 --> 00:29:44.375
<i>and Lestat was my coal fire.</i>

650
00:29:44.838 --> 00:29:47.208
<i>And I found myself
for the very first time.</i>

651
00:29:47.650 --> 00:29:49.333
<i>to anyone other than Paul.</i>

652
00:29:49.876 --> 00:29:52.666
<i>confiding my struggles
to another man.</i>

653
00:29:55.962 --> 00:29:58.292
<i>I was being hunted.</i>

654
00:29:59.430 --> 00:30:02.917
<i>And I was completely unaware
it was happening...</i>

655
00:30:06.167 --> 00:30:06.979
I'm switchin' rooms.

656
00:30:07.004 --> 00:30:09.475
I don't need to hear you
and your good man making noise.

657
00:30:09.500 --> 00:30:10.776
You'd have to be
home to hear that.

658
00:30:10.801 --> 00:30:11.904
I come home nights... !

659
00:30:11.928 --> 00:30:13.291
You come home <i>some</i> nights.

660
00:30:13.612 --> 00:30:15.892
Out cattin' with some
white man. I hear.

661
00:30:15.965 --> 00:30:17.158
He ain't white.
he French.

662
00:30:17.183 --> 00:30:17.750
<i>Oh. </i>

663
00:30:18.245 --> 00:30:19.666
That's a new kind
of white. is it?

664
00:30:19.954 --> 00:30:20.792
French white?

665
00:30:21.253 --> 00:30:22.083
He different.

666
00:30:22.488 --> 00:30:23.792
Invite him
over for dinner.

667
00:30:24.583 --> 00:30:26.000
Mother loves <i>European</i>.

668
00:30:26.625 --> 00:30:29.136
I'm gon' tell Levi you fishin'
for a richer man -- !

669
00:30:29.161 --> 00:30:29.600
Don't.

670
00:30:29.908 --> 00:30:31.541
Don't deny your sister.

671
00:30:31.864 --> 00:30:33.792
I wanna meet
this <i>French white.</i>

672
00:30:36.542 --> 00:30:37.970
I'm just trying to give you
the word of the Lord.

673
00:30:38.208 --> 00:30:40.983
Understa-- Yes. Yes. No.

674
00:30:41.458 --> 00:30:42.379
That is never my --

675
00:30:42.404 --> 00:30:44.667
Paul crawled up
on my bed last night.

676
00:30:51.333 --> 00:30:52.875
Wept for good near an hour.

677
00:30:53.700 --> 00:30:55.166
He ain't takin' it.
you gettin' married.

678
00:30:58.167 --> 00:30:59.853
Levi told me of a place

679
00:31:00.364 --> 00:31:01.250
over in Gretna.

680
00:31:02.028 --> 00:31:03.583
takes in men like Paul.

681
00:31:04.083 --> 00:31:05.433
It's not some
crazy person's house like --

682
00:31:05.458 --> 00:31:06.875
How'd that work
last time. huh?

683
00:31:07.266 --> 00:31:08.792
He come out
worse than before.

684
00:31:09.583 --> 00:31:10.208
Gretna.

685
00:31:10.693 --> 00:31:11.667
It ain't happenin'.

686
00:31:12.667 --> 00:31:14.267
He died on
the cross for you.

687
00:31:14.292 --> 00:31:15.933
Yes...you.

688
00:31:16.208 --> 00:31:16.958
I worry.

689
00:31:17.417 --> 00:31:17.931
I worry so much --

690
00:31:17.955 --> 00:31:19.209
Worry about your own life.

691
00:31:21.576 --> 00:31:23.084
Worry about
being a bride.

692
00:31:25.411 --> 00:31:27.291
Worry about
what you gon' wear

693
00:31:28.154 --> 00:31:29.292
in London.

694
00:31:30.044 --> 00:31:31.068
in Paris.

695
00:31:31.146 --> 00:31:32.060
Florence.

696
00:31:34.645 --> 00:31:36.106
- What is this... ?

697
00:31:33.208 --> 00:31:34.927
Now. y'all gon' be in
steerage outta New York.

698
00:31:35.263 --> 00:31:36.250
but once you
get to Europe.

699
00:31:36.403 --> 00:31:37.774
it's first class on boats.

700
00:31:37.798 --> 00:31:39.375
trains. and hotel rooms.

701
00:31:38.911 --> 00:31:40.899
- What did you go and do?

702
00:31:41.451 --> 00:31:42.622
You should put the band
by the deck

703
00:31:42.763 --> 00:31:44.667
and the food
by the fountain.

704
00:31:50.142 --> 00:31:51.250
Mamaw!

705
00:31:51.978 --> 00:31:53.875
I'm goin' 'round the world!

706
00:32:04.083 --> 00:32:06.333
I can't thank you enough.
Mama du Lac.

707
00:32:06.525 --> 00:32:07.877
I never been east of Alabama.

708
00:32:07.902 --> 00:32:09.378
and now I'm going
to see the pyramids.

709
00:32:09.862 --> 00:32:12.142
Oh. I think every
young family deserves

710
00:32:12.167 --> 00:32:13.459
a little adventure.

711
00:32:13.917 --> 00:32:15.709
Wouldn't you say.
Monsieur Lioncourt?

712
00:32:15.734 --> 00:32:16.750
Oui. Madame.

713
00:32:17.065 --> 00:32:18.042
My mother.

714
00:32:18.300 --> 00:32:20.147
she gave me
every advantage in life

715
00:32:20.267 --> 00:32:21.083
as a young man.

716
00:32:21.216 --> 00:32:22.983
My first Mastiff.

717
00:32:23.007 --> 00:32:24.542
first flintlock rifle.

718
00:32:24.812 --> 00:32:26.260
the means to make
my way to <i>Paris.</i>

719
00:32:26.347 --> 00:32:28.584
It was Louis that purchased
your holiday. Levi.

720
00:32:28.958 --> 00:32:30.583
It's Louis who controls
the money.

721
00:32:30.216 --> 00:32:31.182
- Pay no mind. Levi.

722
00:32:31.214 --> 00:32:32.542
And I don't know
who gave you the right

723
00:32:32.567 --> 00:32:33.552
to call our mother
your mother.

724
00:32:33.652 --> 00:32:34.853
She's not your mother yet

725
00:32:34.953 --> 00:32:36.958
and will never be
your scientific mother.

726
00:32:37.023 --> 00:32:38.083
Paul...

727
00:32:40.667 --> 00:32:42.183
I do love this
<i>bouillabaisse</i>.

728
00:32:42.333 --> 00:32:43.166
Wha?!

729
00:32:44.696 --> 00:32:46.417
Down here.
we call it <i>gumbo</i>.

730
00:32:46.885 --> 00:32:48.919
We had a gumbo the other night.
didn't we. Louis?

731
00:32:48.944 --> 00:32:50.166
Uh. right after the opera.

732
00:32:50.202 --> 00:32:52.225
<i>Ohh</i>. we've got Louis
to an opera... ?

733
00:32:52.375 --> 00:32:53.061
<i>"Iolanta."</i>

734
00:32:53.086 --> 00:32:54.897
'Bout some blind princess.

735
00:32:54.967 --> 00:32:56.750
didn't know
she was a princess.

736
00:32:57.132 --> 00:32:59.232
Stomach got grumblin'.
left halfway through.

737
00:32:59.257 --> 00:33:01.280
And what exactly is the nature
 of your relationship

738
00:33:01.305 --> 00:33:03.875
with my my brother.
<i>Monsieur Lioncourt</i>?

739
00:33:10.929 --> 00:33:13.125
Your brother and I
have been discussing

740
00:33:13.225 --> 00:33:15.042
a few investment
opportunities.

741
00:33:15.833 --> 00:33:17.583
The birds asked me
to ask you.

742
00:33:18.458 --> 00:33:19.875
I wasn't being rude.

743
00:33:22.788 --> 00:33:23.612
<i>Monsieur Freniere</i>.

744
00:33:24.167 --> 00:33:27.767
would you tell me how you came to
propose to this delightsome young woman?

745
00:33:27.792 --> 00:33:29.176
Oh. that's
a good yarn.

746
00:33:29.201 --> 00:33:32.167
Are you one with Christ.
<i>Monsieur Lioncourt</i>?

747
00:33:31.530 --> 00:33:33.292
- How 'bout you shut
your damn mouth?

748
00:33:33.912 --> 00:33:34.760
Louis.

749
00:33:35.046 --> 00:33:36.716
That's alright.
Louis. Madame.

750
00:33:36.908 --> 00:33:38.154
"The birds speak for him."

751
00:33:41.750 --> 00:33:43.049
I came to know Christ

752
00:33:43.370 --> 00:33:44.417
in a monastery.

753
00:33:46.968 --> 00:33:48.667
I wanted
to be a priest.

754
00:33:49.833 --> 00:33:51.250
Just like you. Paul.

755
00:33:52.757 --> 00:33:55.850
And under the guidance and
discipline of the monks who lived there.

756
00:33:56.500 --> 00:33:58.667
I came to memorize
both the testaments.

757
00:33:59.371 --> 00:34:00.833
the writings of Assisi.

758
00:34:01.417 --> 00:34:02.292
Aquinas.

759
00:34:03.046 --> 00:34:04.000
Erasmus.

760
00:34:04.537 --> 00:34:05.934
all the saints and scholars.

761
00:34:10.030 --> 00:34:11.250
My father.

762
00:34:11.819 --> 00:34:13.083
a vulgar man.

763
00:34:13.585 --> 00:34:15.542
did not think much
of this education.

764
00:34:16.444 --> 00:34:19.500
and so he and my brothers
conspired to pull me out.

765
00:34:21.155 --> 00:34:22.557
lock me away.

766
00:34:23.616 --> 00:34:25.045
where.
between beatings.

767
00:34:25.101 --> 00:34:26.041
starvations.

768
00:34:26.272 --> 00:34:27.558
and the failure of Christ

769
00:34:27.583 --> 00:34:29.599
to intercede the beatings
and starvations.

770
00:34:29.624 --> 00:34:32.458
I slowly forgot... all about
the testaments.

771
00:34:32.483 --> 00:34:33.280
Assisi.

772
00:34:33.600 --> 00:34:34.198
Aquinas.

773
00:34:34.229 --> 00:34:35.545
Erasmus.

774
00:34:35.569 --> 00:34:36.250
all of it.

775
00:34:36.151 --> 00:34:36.459
<i>Stop.</i>

776
00:34:36.484 --> 00:34:36.979
And so.

777
00:34:37.003 --> 00:34:38.542
to answer your boring question.

778
00:34:38.567 --> 00:34:41.000
there is an <i>ocean</i>
between Christ and myself!

779
00:34:41.088 --> 00:34:41.708
Stop!

780
00:34:41.233 --> 00:34:45.083
<i>J'espère que cela satisfera les oiseaux perchés dans la cage de votre esprit!</i>

781
00:34:45.208 --> 00:34:46.537
<i>Don't do that shit here!</i>

782
00:34:49.405 --> 00:34:50.500
Not with my family.

783
00:34:52.104 --> 00:34:52.959
You understand?

784
00:35:01.950 --> 00:35:05.750
I am cursed with my father's
temper at times.

785
00:35:06.772 --> 00:35:08.500
and the rudeness is all mine.

786
00:35:09.007 --> 00:35:10.242
Florence:
That's alright.

787
00:35:10.625 --> 00:35:12.744
It's the humidity.
It does that sometimes.

788
00:35:13.000 --> 00:35:14.546
Why don't we have
some ice wine?

789
00:35:15.518 --> 00:35:16.534
And Levi here.

790
00:35:16.787 --> 00:35:18.725
can tell us all again

791
00:35:18.750 --> 00:35:22.208
how he won my
joychild's heart.

792
00:35:26.061 --> 00:35:28.708
I fear your family has taken
a permanent offense at me.

793
00:35:29.995 --> 00:35:31.772
When Paul
ain't pickin' at his plate.

794
00:35:31.917 --> 00:35:32.917
he pickin' a fight.

795
00:35:33.708 --> 00:35:35.708
If I had your tricks.
I'd have done the same.

796
00:35:36.034 --> 00:35:37.250
You must envy him.

797
00:35:37.842 --> 00:35:40.167
The boy thinks God speaks to him
through birds in his head.

798
00:35:40.206 --> 00:35:41.542
How d'you figure <i>envy</i>?

799
00:35:41.951 --> 00:35:43.708
The liberty he has
with his thoughts.

800
00:35:44.009 --> 00:35:45.767
However misshapen
they may be.

801
00:35:45.792 --> 00:35:47.709
your brother has no shame
in sharing them.

802
00:35:47.713 --> 00:35:49.083
You sayin' I got <i>shame</i>?

803
00:35:49.499 --> 00:35:52.000
The lie you told about leaving
the opera house early.

804
00:35:52.375 --> 00:35:54.042
You were near weeping
when the curtain fell.

805
00:35:54.386 --> 00:35:55.792
Why hide that
from your family?

806
00:35:56.322 --> 00:35:58.083
Don't everybody need
to know what I do.

807
00:35:58.590 --> 00:36:00.125
Dishonesty
breeds dishonesty.

808
00:36:00.764 --> 00:36:01.875
They sit
in judgment.

809
00:36:02.417 --> 00:36:04.192
Paul is the only one
to say it to my face.

810
00:36:04.217 --> 00:36:06.041
but I know my ma
and Grace think it. too.

811
00:36:06.612 --> 00:36:08.842
My daddy ran our sugar business
into a swamp.

812
00:36:08.867 --> 00:36:11.917
When he passed.
we was four months --

813
00:36:12.037 --> 00:36:14.306
<i>four months</i> from going bankrupt

814
00:36:14.330 --> 00:36:15.625
if I didn't do something.

815
00:36:16.125 --> 00:36:18.292
You don't need to defend
yourself to me. Louis.

816
00:36:18.577 --> 00:36:20.419
I know what you go through
to keep your family

817
00:36:20.546 --> 00:36:21.847
ignorant in their comfort.

818
00:36:21.947 --> 00:36:23.667
It ain't easy.
the work I do.

819
00:36:24.250 --> 00:36:26.162
Nothing but broken souls
around me.

820
00:36:26.216 --> 00:36:27.417
and the ones that
ain't broke

821
00:36:27.701 --> 00:36:28.583
are greedy.

822
00:36:29.237 --> 00:36:30.250
Bone-tired.

823
00:36:32.167 --> 00:36:33.542
Drink up. my good man.

824
00:36:34.167 --> 00:36:35.709
The Earth's
a savage garden.

825
00:36:41.333 --> 00:36:43.750
You did good gettin' off
that boat when you did.

826
00:36:44.500 --> 00:36:46.250
St. Louis is
dull as dishwater.

827
00:36:47.750 --> 00:36:48.292
Yes.

828
00:36:48.631 --> 00:36:50.162
I feel quite at home here.

829
00:36:51.917 --> 00:36:52.917
Shall we have a nightcap?

830
00:36:54.446 --> 00:36:55.500
Um...

831
00:36:56.750 --> 00:36:58.333
Probably had
enough for tonight.

832
00:36:59.208 --> 00:37:01.166
Gotta make my rounds
back on Liberty.

833
00:37:01.587 --> 00:37:02.750
You must. Louis.

834
00:37:03.750 --> 00:37:04.917
I bought you a gift.

835
00:37:06.410 --> 00:37:07.250
A gift?

836
00:37:08.660 --> 00:37:09.583
A flower.

837
00:37:38.762 --> 00:37:40.542
That's a nice music box
you got there.

838
00:37:41.215 --> 00:37:42.746
It's one of the few things
I brought with me

839
00:37:42.771 --> 00:37:43.750
from the continent.

840
00:37:45.441 --> 00:37:46.750
What's that
lil' song playin'?

841
00:37:47.132 --> 00:37:47.917
Do you like it?

842
00:37:49.002 --> 00:37:52.292
I composed it for a young
violinist I once knew.

843
00:37:53.080 --> 00:37:55.583
a boy of infinite beauty
and sensitivity.

844
00:37:58.417 --> 00:38:00.417
I believe that is for
the lips. Miss Lily.

845
00:38:01.054 --> 00:38:02.875
I don't like the way
mine look plain.

846
00:38:04.356 --> 00:38:06.292
And Mr. du Lac
don't mind when I do it.

847
00:38:06.552 --> 00:38:07.417
Mm-hmm.

848
00:38:08.379 --> 00:38:09.958
A pair of
misfit beauties.

849
00:38:11.357 --> 00:38:13.708
I can see why you both run
to the other.

850
00:38:14.869 --> 00:38:16.375
Miss Carroll know
you're here. Lily?

851
00:38:17.402 --> 00:38:19.142
I can assure you.
the <i>Fairplay</i> has been

852
00:38:19.167 --> 00:38:21.250
handsomely compensated
for the evening.

853
00:38:23.292 --> 00:38:25.375
Sent a two-horse carriage
to pick me up.

854
00:38:25.795 --> 00:38:27.791
Felt like the Queen
of the Quarter!

855
00:38:31.750 --> 00:38:33.133
I told Mr. Lioncourt.

856
00:38:33.933 --> 00:38:35.625
you and me usually just talk.

857
00:38:36.181 --> 00:38:37.583
And why is that. Louis?

858
00:38:38.208 --> 00:38:41.000
What kind of a man
wastes this waist with words?

859
00:38:43.418 --> 00:38:44.625
A beautiful man.

860
00:38:51.708 --> 00:38:53.291
There's nothing to be
nervous about.

861
00:38:53.875 --> 00:38:55.312
The curtains are closed.

862
00:38:55.336 --> 00:38:57.125
the servants sent home.

863
00:38:58.042 --> 00:39:00.459
Even the planets and stars
are blindfolded.

864
00:39:01.134 --> 00:39:02.273
That's your thing. then?

865
00:39:02.781 --> 00:39:04.000
You like to watch?

866
00:39:07.121 --> 00:39:09.333
<i>I've been watching you
for some time now. Louis.</i>

867
00:39:09.792 --> 00:39:11.164
<i>From river to lake.</i>

868
00:39:11.333 --> 00:39:12.625
<i>lake back to river.</i>

869
00:39:13.244 --> 00:39:15.125
<i>looking for
my companion heart.</i>

870
00:39:15.238 --> 00:39:16.334
How d'you do that?

871
00:39:16.917 --> 00:39:17.542
Do what?

872
00:39:17.987 --> 00:39:18.917
<i>Do what?</i>

873
00:39:19.458 --> 00:39:21.125
Get in my head
like that...

874
00:39:22.208 --> 00:39:23.500
<i>Such a pretty head.</i>

875
00:40:13.996 --> 00:40:15.250
That's fine. love.

876
00:40:26.875 --> 00:40:28.242
<i>Dormez bien.</i>

877
00:40:28.359 --> 00:40:29.333
<i>Miss Lily.</i>

878
00:41:59.000 --> 00:42:00.207
<i>It bears repeating.</i>

879
00:42:00.231 --> 00:42:01.687
<i>I did not consider myself</i>

880
00:42:01.787 --> 00:42:04.208
a homosexual man.
at the time.

881
00:42:05.250 --> 00:42:07.625
I mean.
I had had experiences.

882
00:42:08.273 --> 00:42:08.942
Guilt.

883
00:42:09.208 --> 00:42:10.166
shame.

884
00:42:10.833 --> 00:42:14.416
floating-on-a-sea-of-vodka
type encounters.

885
00:42:15.333 --> 00:42:17.051
Obviously. I've come to embrace

886
00:42:17.075 --> 00:42:18.375
my sexuality.

887
00:42:19.336 --> 00:42:20.205
'Course. you know that.

888
00:42:20.305 --> 00:42:22.225
We met at a gay bar.
didn't we. Daniel?

889
00:42:22.679 --> 00:42:23.835
It was a good place
to score.

890
00:42:23.860 --> 00:42:25.209
I did what I had to.

891
00:42:26.208 --> 00:42:27.125
You've been married?

892
00:42:27.958 --> 00:42:28.833
Twice.

893
00:42:30.221 --> 00:42:31.692
But we're not here for me.

894
00:42:31.840 --> 00:42:32.625
are we?

895
00:42:34.625 --> 00:42:36.043
When you were using drugs.

896
00:42:36.461 --> 00:42:37.625
Mr. Molloy.

897
00:42:38.365 --> 00:42:41.250
do you remember
the <i>best you ever had</i>?

898
00:42:42.500 --> 00:42:44.058
Berkeley. 1978.

899
00:42:44.083 --> 00:42:47.750
Some Mexican black tar that
Carly and Pedro were slinging.

900
00:42:48.239 --> 00:42:49.183
So.

901
00:42:49.385 --> 00:42:50.708
imagine that.

902
00:42:51.125 --> 00:42:53.125
flowing inside
your veins again.

903
00:42:54.750 --> 00:42:55.500
Now.

904
00:42:56.267 --> 00:42:57.525
multiply it.

905
00:42:58.220 --> 00:42:59.353
by <i>miles</i>.

906
00:42:59.720 --> 00:43:02.334
to the <i>rings of Saturn
and back...</i>

907
00:43:07.792 --> 00:43:10.889
<i>He had taken what
he called</i> "un petit coup" --

908
00:43:11.212 --> 00:43:12.334
<i>the Little Drink.</i>

909
00:43:12.875 --> 00:43:14.292
<i>Not enough to kill me.</i>

910
00:43:14.750 --> 00:43:17.542
<i>but just enough
to keep him fit.</i>

911
00:43:18.458 --> 00:43:22.458
<i>It takes an enormous amount
of restraint for us.</i>

912
00:43:22.792 --> 00:43:24.000
<i>the Little Drink.</i>

913
00:43:24.735 --> 00:43:25.875
<i>For a human.</i>

914
00:43:26.337 --> 00:43:28.188
<i>experiencing it
for the first time.</i>

915
00:43:28.306 --> 00:43:29.584
<i>it was...</i>

916
00:43:29.841 --> 00:43:31.208
<i>... unsettling.</i>

917
00:43:31.798 --> 00:43:34.640
<i>And not for the physical toll
on my body.</i>

918
00:43:34.665 --> 00:43:36.125
<i>which was significant.</i>

919
00:43:36.625 --> 00:43:41.086
<i>but for the feelings of
intimacy. it awoke within me.</i>

920
00:43:43.806 --> 00:43:46.290
<i>I had</i> never
<i>allowed myself</i>

921
00:43:46.417 --> 00:43:48.542
<i>to feel emotionally close
to anyone.</i>

922
00:43:48.728 --> 00:43:50.125
<i>much less a man.</i>

923
00:43:50.833 --> 00:43:54.291
<i>I had no</i> room <i>for feelings
like these in my life.</i>

924
00:43:55.876 --> 00:43:58.417
<i>You could be a lot of things
in New Orleans.</i>

925
00:43:59.000 --> 00:44:02.875
<i>but an openly gay. Negro man
was not one of 'em.</i>

926
00:44:05.407 --> 00:44:07.750
<i>I vowed never to return again.</i>

927
00:44:08.625 --> 00:44:11.458
<i>I shut that night
out of my mind</i>

928
00:44:12.091 --> 00:44:15.292
<i>and turned my attentions back
to life as it was before.</i>

929
00:44:17.417 --> 00:44:21.250
One. two. three. jump!

930
00:44:37.696 --> 00:44:38.416
Hold still now.

931
00:44:38.509 --> 00:44:40.333
We are missing
my father today.

932
00:44:41.040 --> 00:44:42.981
He's supposed to dance with me
to start the night off.

933
00:44:44.708 --> 00:44:46.083
I'm trying not to cry now.

934
00:44:47.208 --> 00:44:49.475
And I thought the best
way to honour Daddy

935
00:44:49.750 --> 00:44:51.375
would be to make my brothers
do the work.

936
00:44:53.291 --> 00:44:54.500
Mm-hmm.

937
00:44:54.726 --> 00:44:56.494
Half of y'all
don't know this.

938
00:44:56.708 --> 00:44:58.196
but these no-good boys.

939
00:44:58.221 --> 00:45:00.306
used to shuffle for
pennies on Sunday!

940
00:45:00.899 --> 00:45:04.267
Called themselves
"The ABCDEFGs".

941
00:45:05.167 --> 00:45:06.433
Remember that. Father Matthias?

942
00:45:06.458 --> 00:45:07.138
Oh. yes.

943
00:45:07.162 --> 00:45:07.806
ABCDE -- ?

944
00:45:07.906 --> 00:45:09.440
"Alter Boys Come Dancing

945
00:45:09.540 --> 00:45:11.392
Every day For God."

946
00:45:13.060 --> 00:45:14.392
I remember
their collection <i>hat</i>

947
00:45:14.417 --> 00:45:16.177
didn't always make it
to the collection <i>plate</i>.

948
00:45:16.500 --> 00:45:17.417
That's right.

949
00:45:18.449 --> 00:45:19.375
Paul. Louis?

950
00:45:19.792 --> 00:45:21.452
Oh. come on. now.
Please!

951
00:45:21.552 --> 00:45:23.750
Hey. now.
Come on. please!

952
00:45:24.756 --> 00:45:25.750
It's for me.

953
00:45:25.903 --> 00:45:27.166
on my wedding day.

954
00:45:26.607 --> 00:45:27.497
- Come on. brother.

955
00:45:29.896 --> 00:45:31.625
Alright!

956
00:45:40.500 --> 00:45:41.542
Shoes are tight.

957
00:45:41.739 --> 00:45:42.939
Oh. the shoes is fine.

958
00:45:42.963 --> 00:45:44.167
It's the feet that's fat.

959
00:45:45.943 --> 00:45:47.591
Hey. what kinda
rhythm you want. boss?

960
00:45:47.767 --> 00:45:49.791
Just play it loud
so they can't hear our feet.

961
00:45:54.585 --> 00:45:56.458
Alright.
What you remember?

962
00:45:58.323 --> 00:45:59.667
Maybe. um...

963
00:46:01.759 --> 00:46:02.833
Hey. come on.

964
00:46:06.164 --> 00:46:08.533
-Hey!
-Go ahead now!

965
00:46:13.839 --> 00:46:16.374
-Whoo!
-Hey! Hey!

966
00:46:22.881 --> 00:46:25.542
Alright! Okay!

967
00:46:29.220 --> 00:46:30.788
They still got it!

968
00:46:35.326 --> 00:46:37.667
-Oh!
-Yeah!

969
00:46:41.583 --> 00:46:43.416
Okay. You ain't gon' do it.

970
00:46:44.000 --> 00:46:45.146
You ain't gon' do it... !

971
00:46:57.333 --> 00:46:58.416
That's right!

972
00:47:37.662 --> 00:47:38.517
We gonna miss it.

973
00:47:38.542 --> 00:47:40.542
Quit talkin'.
I have to concentrate.

974
00:47:41.250 --> 00:47:44.167
It's them three pieces of
checkered cake holding you back.

975
00:47:44.667 --> 00:47:46.462
Five pieces of checkered cake.

976
00:47:47.125 --> 00:47:48.375
the Pompano fillet.

977
00:47:48.779 --> 00:47:50.376
three boudins.

978
00:47:50.400 --> 00:47:51.330
dirty rice.

979
00:47:52.054 --> 00:47:52.529
beef.

980
00:47:52.667 --> 00:47:53.542
green beans.

981
00:47:54.193 --> 00:47:55.670
five.
six wines.

982
00:47:57.357 --> 00:47:58.113
Eat anything else.

983
00:47:58.138 --> 00:47:59.920
the buttons on your vest
gon' pop off

984
00:47:59.945 --> 00:48:01.411
like cannon balls.

985
00:48:01.833 --> 00:48:03.166
take down
the neighbourhood.

986
00:48:12.857 --> 00:48:15.834
9.517.

987
00:48:16.542 --> 00:48:18.125
That's how many days
we've been in his house.

988
00:48:18.792 --> 00:48:20.667
You do that math
all by yourself?

989
00:48:21.875 --> 00:48:23.234
You remember the day
I got taller than you?

990
00:48:23.334 --> 00:48:24.369
Always bringin'
that up.

991
00:48:24.469 --> 00:48:26.292
Shot up like
a Nuttall oak.

992
00:48:26.917 --> 00:48:29.267
Daddy said I was gon' look down
on you for the rest of days.

993
00:48:29.299 --> 00:48:30.299
Yeah. yeah...

994
00:48:30.667 --> 00:48:31.497
Half an inch.

995
00:48:31.583 --> 00:48:33.250
That was a good month.
that month.

996
00:48:38.458 --> 00:48:40.083
I think you should
get married next.

997
00:48:41.042 --> 00:48:41.886
Do you now?

998
00:48:42.292 --> 00:48:43.521
And you should
marry Hazel.

999
00:48:43.583 --> 00:48:45.083
Hazel? Who that?

1000
00:48:45.414 --> 00:48:47.292
The one you were dancing
too close with.

1001
00:48:48.084 --> 00:48:50.000
You dance that close.
you ought to be married.

1002
00:48:51.000 --> 00:48:52.417
I didn't catch her name.

1003
00:48:52.958 --> 00:48:54.583
Well. it's Hazel.

1004
00:49:02.286 --> 00:49:04.334
You still doing business
with that man Lestat?

1005
00:49:06.250 --> 00:49:08.208
Nah.
Didn't work out.

1006
00:49:10.625 --> 00:49:11.333
That's good.

1007
00:49:13.208 --> 00:49:14.058
'Cause he the Devil.

1008
00:49:14.083 --> 00:49:15.558
You think everyone's
the Devil.

1009
00:49:15.583 --> 00:49:17.833
He's here to take souls.
He told me so.

1010
00:49:18.625 --> 00:49:20.654
He spoke to me
without moving his lips.

1011
00:49:21.021 --> 00:49:22.542
He got tricks is all.

1012
00:49:24.667 --> 00:49:26.990
Mortal sins must be
confessed. Louis.

1013
00:49:27.125 --> 00:49:28.875
Ain't never gon' see him
again. Paul.

1014
00:49:34.958 --> 00:49:36.541
You think Levi
loves her enough?

1015
00:49:37.060 --> 00:49:38.541
You know. Grace
needs a lot of love.

1016
00:49:40.140 --> 00:49:41.208
I do.

1017
00:49:41.875 --> 00:49:44.333
Do you think he's givin' her
everything he's got inside him?

1018
00:49:46.717 --> 00:49:47.417
Mm-hmm.

1019
00:49:55.638 --> 00:49:57.541
Mother made a good party
for Grace.

1020
00:49:57.842 --> 00:49:58.792
Mm-hmm. yeah.

1021
00:49:58.892 --> 00:50:01.042
Yeah. they gon' talk
about this one for years.

1022
00:50:01.370 --> 00:50:02.037
Yeah.

1023
00:50:09.042 --> 00:50:10.000
I love you. Louis.

1024
00:50:10.216 --> 00:50:11.875
And I love you. too.
baby brother.

1025
00:50:19.920 --> 00:50:21.500
I ate too much
checkered cake.

1026
00:50:26.747 --> 00:50:27.292
Paul.

1027
00:50:29.941 --> 00:50:30.542
Paul!

1028
00:50:33.875 --> 00:50:34.875
<i>Paul -- !</i>

1029
00:50:36.185 --> 00:50:37.384
Oh. my lord!

1030
00:50:37.424 --> 00:50:38.417
Paul!

1031
00:50:41.271 --> 00:50:43.500
That was the last sunrise
I ever saw.

1032
00:50:45.158 --> 00:50:47.834
Perhaps the kindest thing
the Dark Gift has given me.

1033
00:50:53.086 --> 00:50:54.458
I don't miss the sun.

1034
00:50:56.542 --> 00:50:58.459
the reminders it carries.

1035
00:51:18.810 --> 00:51:20.056
I have seen death

1036
00:51:20.318 --> 00:51:20.955
over.

1037
00:51:21.202 --> 00:51:22.267
and over.

1038
00:51:22.292 --> 00:51:23.447
and over

1039
00:51:23.471 --> 00:51:25.209
and over again.

1040
00:51:26.568 --> 00:51:27.667
It's <i>boring</i>.

1041
00:51:28.295 --> 00:51:29.792
That'll make
a great blurb.

1042
00:51:30.625 --> 00:51:33.090
The diagnosis
you received. Daniel.

1043
00:51:33.493 --> 00:51:34.575
It winds your clock.

1044
00:51:36.625 --> 00:51:38.614
This virus has turned
the world sideways.

1045
00:51:38.639 --> 00:51:39.500
I get it.

1046
00:51:39.912 --> 00:51:41.000
I'm gonna die.

1047
00:51:41.458 --> 00:51:42.583
<i>They're</i> gonna die.

1048
00:51:43.631 --> 00:51:44.702
But not the Vampire.

1049
00:51:44.802 --> 00:51:46.375
The Vampire is <i>bored.</i>

1050
00:51:48.811 --> 00:51:50.667
The human was destroyed.

1051
00:51:52.667 --> 00:51:54.209
Utterly destroyed.

1052
00:51:55.542 --> 00:51:56.750
I was at the funeral home.

1053
00:51:57.405 --> 00:51:59.016
Everything is going
as it should.

1054
00:51:59.375 --> 00:52:00.330
Good men there.

1055
00:52:01.248 --> 00:52:02.333
Promised me that --

1056
00:52:02.358 --> 00:52:04.083
You musta said something
to him. Louis.

1057
00:52:04.875 --> 00:52:06.558
You musta said
something to him

1058
00:52:06.700 --> 00:52:08.292
to make him do that
to himself.

1059
00:52:10.108 --> 00:52:12.417
Paul slipped and fell.
Florence.

1060
00:52:13.167 --> 00:52:14.975
I don't think this is something
you want to pursue.

1061
00:52:15.000 --> 00:52:16.292
He was a fragile boy.

1062
00:52:17.958 --> 00:52:19.083
He always was.

1063
00:52:22.139 --> 00:52:23.000
And you.

1064
00:52:23.750 --> 00:52:25.808
you always had
to have the last word.

1065
00:52:25.833 --> 00:52:26.708
didn't you. Louis?

1066
00:52:27.083 --> 00:52:28.873
You always had to take him
down a peg.

1067
00:52:28.987 --> 00:52:29.875
<i>Mamaw.</i>

1068
00:52:31.642 --> 00:52:32.684
What did you say
to him?

1069
00:52:33.500 --> 00:52:34.875
Why was you
even up there?

1070
00:52:36.373 --> 00:52:38.292
Watchin' the sun
come up. Mama.

1071
00:52:42.100 --> 00:52:43.885
You don't get past the gates.

1072
00:52:44.326 --> 00:52:45.833
iffen you kill yourself... !

1073
00:52:46.764 --> 00:52:48.000
Don't you know that?

1074
00:52:49.264 --> 00:52:50.875
Paul gone down
the other way.

1075
00:52:52.606 --> 00:52:54.417
Paul's in <i>Hell</i>
because of you.

1076
00:53:06.500 --> 00:53:08.737
<i>Storyville lowered their hats.</i>

1077
00:53:08.784 --> 00:53:11.500
<i>gave their propers.
because it was custom.</i>

1078
00:53:11.917 --> 00:53:14.666
<i>But if you look past
those lined up on the sidewalk.</i>

1079
00:53:14.737 --> 00:53:17.027
<i>you'd see the bars
hadn't stopped serving.</i>

1080
00:53:17.292 --> 00:53:19.417
<i>the whores
hadn't stopped whoring.</i>

1081
00:53:19.833 --> 00:53:21.583
<i>What was Paul's life
worth to them?</i>

1082
00:53:21.958 --> 00:53:23.500
<i>What was my life worth?</i>

1083
00:53:23.958 --> 00:53:25.924
<i>The Big Man of Liberty Street.</i>

1084
00:53:26.011 --> 00:53:29.459
<i>trailing the satin-lined
evidence of his failure.</i>

1085
00:53:30.472 --> 00:53:33.125
<i>Easy prey for
the discerning predator.</i>

1086
00:53:37.377 --> 00:53:38.459
An elegant coffin.

1087
00:53:38.484 --> 00:53:39.518
Would you tell me
where you purchased --

1088
00:53:39.650 --> 00:53:40.500
Move on.

1089
00:53:40.886 --> 00:53:42.642
I wait on my balcony
every night.

1090
00:53:42.667 --> 00:53:43.616
You've been avoiding me.

1091
00:53:43.640 --> 00:53:45.375
I have been occupied.

1092
00:53:44.422 --> 00:53:47.040
- Miss Lily proved herself
a poor substitute.

1093
00:53:47.065 --> 00:53:49.708
And I don't take kindly
to being avoided.

1094
00:53:48.628 --> 00:53:50.167
- It's my brother's funeral!

1095
00:53:50.284 --> 00:53:51.362
Believe me
when I tell you.

1096
00:53:51.462 --> 00:53:53.252
your brother longed
for that flagstone.

1097
00:53:53.338 --> 00:53:54.625
What'd you say to me?!

1098
00:53:54.846 --> 00:53:55.959
I got it. boss.

1099
00:53:56.222 --> 00:53:57.126
Keep walking.

1100
00:54:05.417 --> 00:54:08.334
<i>Lestat's ambush
had disoriented me.</i>

1101
00:54:09.375 --> 00:54:12.125
<i>The sermon that was given.
I could not hear.</i>

1102
00:54:13.729 --> 00:54:16.041
<i>And when the gathering
cut loose the body.</i>

1103
00:54:16.687 --> 00:54:18.506
<i>I could not join
the transformation</i>

1104
00:54:18.531 --> 00:54:20.083
<i>of those in attendance.</i>

1105
00:54:21.859 --> 00:54:24.125
<i>He would not let me.</i>

1106
00:54:25.444 --> 00:54:26.750
<i>Come to me.</i>

1107
00:54:29.080 --> 00:54:30.292
<i>Come to me.</i>

1108
00:54:31.135 --> 00:54:31.792
No.

1109
00:54:39.792 --> 00:54:41.084
Walk you home. Mama?

1110
00:54:41.540 --> 00:54:43.208
No. thank you.

1111
00:54:44.139 --> 00:54:45.917
Levi.
do you mind?

1112
00:54:47.667 --> 00:54:48.917
Of course.
Mama Du Lac.

1113
00:54:53.583 --> 00:54:54.933
She didn't mean
nothin' by it.

1114
00:54:54.958 --> 00:54:55.916
Oh. but she did now.

1115
00:54:55.693 --> 00:54:57.625
- She just needs
to put it somewhere.

1116
00:54:59.229 --> 00:55:00.625
Don't let it inside.

1117
00:55:05.381 --> 00:55:06.625
See you
back at the wake?

1118
00:55:12.830 --> 00:55:14.375
<i>Come to me.</i>

1119
00:55:15.717 --> 00:55:17.708
<i>I did not go to the wake.</i>

1120
00:55:20.000 --> 00:55:22.583
<i>I did not want to face
my mother's blame...</i>

1121
00:55:25.189 --> 00:55:26.667
<i>...my sister's pity.</i>

1122
00:55:28.304 --> 00:55:30.500
<i>I wanted to grieve alone.</i>

1123
00:55:33.208 --> 00:55:36.333
<i>But he would not
allow it.</i>

1124
00:55:39.500 --> 00:55:40.958
<i>Come to me. Louis.</i>

1125
00:55:44.292 --> 00:55:45.417
<i>Come to me.</i>

1126
00:55:51.582 --> 00:55:52.698
Hello. handsome.

1127
00:55:52.833 --> 00:55:53.750
Sazerac.

1128
00:55:54.013 --> 00:55:56.208
My heart broke when I heard of
your brother's passing.

1129
00:55:56.963 --> 00:55:57.875
Miss Lily.

1130
00:55:58.792 --> 00:55:59.542
Oh. my dear.

1131
00:55:59.658 --> 00:56:01.247
I don't care if she busy
with someone.

1132
00:56:01.272 --> 00:56:02.167
I'll pay more.

1133
00:56:02.424 --> 00:56:03.608
'Cause I like Miss Lily.

1134
00:56:03.819 --> 00:56:05.125
and I need Miss Lily.

1135
00:56:05.417 --> 00:56:06.522
Miss Lily died.

1136
00:56:06.958 --> 00:56:08.041
Mr. du Lac.

1137
00:56:09.199 --> 00:56:10.167
Two weeks ago.

1138
00:56:12.667 --> 00:56:14.084
Police found her
under the docks.

1139
00:56:15.625 --> 00:56:18.500
Said she contracted the fevers
that's been going around.

1140
00:56:19.479 --> 00:56:21.416
Blood went and dried up
inside her.

1141
00:56:22.375 --> 00:56:23.458
<i>Viens à moi.</i>

1142
00:56:26.383 --> 00:56:27.405
Father!

1143
00:56:27.429 --> 00:56:29.183
Father Matthias!

1144
00:56:29.208 --> 00:56:30.494
Help me!

1145
00:56:32.245 --> 00:56:33.534
Help me. please... !

1146
00:56:33.559 --> 00:56:35.643
He's in my head.
Father... !

1147
00:56:37.979 --> 00:56:38.875
The Devil.

1148
00:56:39.604 --> 00:56:40.743
is in New Orleans.

1149
00:56:40.768 --> 00:56:41.975
Calm down. son.

1150
00:56:42.292 --> 00:56:43.000
Catch your breath.

1151
00:56:44.870 --> 00:56:47.083
Bless me. Father.
f-for I have sinned.

1152
00:56:47.604 --> 00:56:50.007
<i>Grievously sinned.</i>

1153
00:56:50.380 --> 00:56:51.584
Sign of the cross. son.

1154
00:57:01.425 --> 00:57:02.584
I'm a drunk. Lord.

1155
00:57:03.042 --> 00:57:03.834
I'm a liar.

1156
00:57:04.250 --> 00:57:05.558
I am a thief. Lord.

1157
00:57:05.583 --> 00:57:07.462
I profit off the miseries
of other men.

1158
00:57:07.487 --> 00:57:08.425
and I do it easy.

1159
00:57:08.526 --> 00:57:10.625
Drugs. liquor. women.

1160
00:57:10.792 --> 00:57:13.542
I-I-I-I lure them in
and grab what they got. Lord.

1161
00:57:13.917 --> 00:57:15.627
I take daughters
with no homes

1162
00:57:15.875 --> 00:57:19.100
and I-I put 'em out
on the street. Lord.

1163
00:57:19.375 --> 00:57:21.947
and I lie to myself.
saying I-I'm giving them a roof

1164
00:57:21.972 --> 00:57:23.933
and food and dollar bills
in they pocket.

1165
00:57:23.958 --> 00:57:26.026
but I look in the mirror.
I know what I am --

1166
00:57:26.250 --> 00:57:28.010
the <i>big man</i>
in the <i>big house</i>.

1167
00:57:28.268 --> 00:57:31.010
stuffin' cotton in my ears
so I can't hear their cries.

1168
00:57:31.167 --> 00:57:33.959
And Lord. I dragged my family
into this mess with me.

1169
00:57:35.458 --> 00:57:37.125
I shame my father.

1170
00:57:38.177 --> 00:57:40.308
I f-- I failed
my brother.

1171
00:57:40.333 --> 00:57:41.125
No. son.

1172
00:57:41.273 --> 00:57:44.183
I lost my mother
and sister.

1173
00:57:44.208 --> 00:57:47.392
and rather than fix it
like a man should. Lord.

1174
00:57:47.417 --> 00:57:49.510
I run like a coward.

1175
00:57:49.667 --> 00:57:51.201
I run to the bottle.

1176
00:57:51.481 --> 00:57:52.619
I run to the grift.

1177
00:57:52.742 --> 00:57:54.869
I run to <i>bad beds.</i>

1178
00:57:55.000 --> 00:57:55.702
I-I..

1179
00:57:55.726 --> 00:57:57.274
<i>I laid down with a man.</i>

1180
00:57:59.250 --> 00:58:01.167
I laid down
with the Devil.

1181
00:58:01.917 --> 00:58:04.209
And he has <i>roots</i> in me.

1182
00:58:04.481 --> 00:58:07.875
all his spindly roots
in me!

1183
00:58:08.150 --> 00:58:11.084
and I can't think
nothin' anymore!

1184
00:58:11.125 --> 00:58:12.155
but his voice!

1185
00:58:12.573 --> 00:58:13.917
and his words!

1186
00:58:14.338 --> 00:58:15.193
Please.

1187
00:58:15.322 --> 00:58:16.725
help me!

1188
00:58:17.083 --> 00:58:18.588
I am weak!

1189
00:58:20.055 --> 00:58:21.533
<i>I wanna die... !</i>

1190
00:58:25.080 --> 00:58:25.708
Oh!

1191
00:58:43.220 --> 00:58:44.792
No!

1192
00:58:49.017 --> 00:58:51.125
Do you think God
heard you. Louis?

1193
00:58:51.322 --> 00:58:53.217
In that tawdry box.

1194
00:58:53.533 --> 00:58:55.267
through this <i>pig vessel.</i>

1195
00:58:55.416 --> 00:58:57.826
this -- this <i>charlatan</i>?

1196
00:58:59.250 --> 00:59:01.667
Do you not see
how unworthy he is?

1197
00:59:02.120 --> 00:59:04.542
How can you humiliate yourself
like this?!

1198
00:59:15.083 --> 00:59:16.333
You killed Lily.

1199
00:59:16.917 --> 00:59:19.500
Cut short that magnificent
life she was living.

1200
00:59:20.124 --> 00:59:21.292
What a tragedy.

1201
00:59:21.659 --> 00:59:23.256
Ain't no fever out there.

1202
00:59:23.486 --> 00:59:24.416
That's you.

1203
00:59:24.629 --> 00:59:26.292
You bringin' the death
to town.

1204
00:59:26.463 --> 00:59:28.542
I give death
to those deserving.

1205
00:59:30.968 --> 00:59:32.167
I'm not the Devil.

1206
00:59:32.837 --> 00:59:34.333
You were wrong
about that.

1207
00:59:36.140 --> 00:59:37.750
But I can give you death.

1208
01:00:30.417 --> 01:00:32.834
This primitive country
has picked you clean.

1209
01:00:33.585 --> 01:00:35.190
It has shackled you

1210
01:00:35.444 --> 01:00:37.083
in permanent exile.

1211
01:00:37.958 --> 01:00:39.500
Every room you enter.

1212
01:00:39.536 --> 01:00:41.345
every hat you are
forced to wear --

1213
01:00:41.370 --> 01:00:43.989
the stern landlord.
the deferential businessman.

1214
01:00:44.014 --> 01:00:45.139
the loyal son --

1215
01:00:45.333 --> 01:00:47.111
all these roles
you conform to

1216
01:00:47.211 --> 01:00:48.958
and none of them
your true nature.

1217
01:00:51.708 --> 01:00:54.958
What rage you must feel
as you choke on your sorrow.

1218
01:00:57.843 --> 01:00:59.875
The first time
I laid eyes on you.

1219
01:01:00.167 --> 01:01:01.709
your beautiful face.

1220
01:01:01.926 --> 01:01:03.667
I saw that sorrow.

1221
01:01:04.394 --> 01:01:05.975
I did not know
how it got there

1222
01:01:06.000 --> 01:01:08.583
or why
it was so <i>voluminous</i>.

1223
01:01:11.617 --> 01:01:14.542
I can take away
that sorrow. Louis.

1224
01:01:16.083 --> 01:01:18.392
I can give you that death

1225
01:01:18.417 --> 01:01:21.678
you begged your feeble.
blind. degenerate.

1226
01:01:21.779 --> 01:01:24.750
non-existent God for.

1227
01:01:25.833 --> 01:01:27.875
But I can do it...

1228
01:01:29.083 --> 01:01:30.291
... joyfully.

1229
01:01:32.542 --> 01:01:34.625
I can swap
this life of shame.

1230
01:01:36.083 --> 01:01:38.262
swap it out
for a dark gift

1231
01:01:38.671 --> 01:01:41.291
and a power you can't
begin to imagine.

1232
01:01:43.958 --> 01:01:46.000
You just have to
ask me for it.

1233
01:01:47.945 --> 01:01:50.500
You just have to nod
your beautiful head...

1234
01:01:51.968 --> 01:01:53.250
... and say yes.

1235
01:01:57.525 --> 01:01:58.792
I love you. Louis.

1236
01:02:00.902 --> 01:02:02.417
You are loved.

1237
01:02:04.750 --> 01:02:06.542
I send my love to you.

1238
01:02:07.458 --> 01:02:09.666
and you send it back
'round to me.

1239
01:02:11.087 --> 01:02:12.666
And this circle.

1240
01:02:14.292 --> 01:02:17.667
this home.
we barely had a glimpse of...

1241
01:02:20.411 --> 01:02:22.946
...  know it frightens me
as much as it does you.

1242
01:02:23.542 --> 01:02:25.633
It is difficult to explain

1243
01:02:25.721 --> 01:02:28.208
how his words disarmed me.

1244
01:02:28.478 --> 01:02:31.122
how efficiently succinct

1245
01:02:31.146 --> 01:02:32.216
and impenetrable

1246
01:02:32.316 --> 01:02:33.958
his argument was.

1247
01:02:34.657 --> 01:02:36.321
All my conceptions.

1248
01:02:36.346 --> 01:02:37.716
even my guilt.

1249
01:02:37.740 --> 01:02:39.437
and my wish to die.

1250
01:02:39.462 --> 01:02:42.000
seemed
utterly unimportant.

1251
01:02:42.292 --> 01:02:44.336
and I completely forgot myself.

1252
01:02:44.428 --> 01:02:47.181
and the <i>barbaric</i> scene
that surrounded me.

1253
01:02:48.181 --> 01:02:50.364
For the first time in my life.

1254
01:02:50.388 --> 01:02:53.871
<i>I was seen.</i>

1255
01:02:54.268 --> 01:02:57.000
Be my companion.
Louis.

1256
01:02:58.375 --> 01:03:00.875
Be all the beautiful
things you are.

1257
01:03:02.357 --> 01:03:04.459
and be them
without apology.

1258
01:03:06.875 --> 01:03:08.417
For all eternity.

1259
01:03:26.118 --> 01:03:27.575
<i>He drained me</i>

1260
01:03:27.935 --> 01:03:30.584
<i>to the very threshold of death.</i>

1261
01:04:02.333 --> 01:04:03.275
<i>The blood.</i>

1262
01:04:04.361 --> 01:04:06.775
<i>it came as a dull roar
at first.</i>

1263
01:04:07.275 --> 01:04:08.792
And then a pounding.

1264
01:04:10.167 --> 01:04:12.042
like the pounding of a drum.

1265
01:04:12.883 --> 01:04:14.325
growing louder.

1266
01:04:14.917 --> 01:04:16.459
and louder.

1267
01:04:17.417 --> 01:04:20.868
as if some... 
enormous creature

1268
01:04:20.892 --> 01:04:25.083
were coming through
a dark and alien forest.

1269
01:04:25.636 --> 01:04:28.007
A huge drum.

1270
01:04:30.000 --> 01:04:30.792
And then.

1271
01:04:31.994 --> 01:04:34.792
<i>there came
a pounding of another drum.</i>

1272
01:04:35.080 --> 01:04:37.947
<i>as if another giant
were coming behind him.</i>

1273
01:04:38.013 --> 01:04:41.697
<i>each giant intent
on his own drum.</i>

1274
01:04:41.837 --> 01:04:44.416
<i>giving no notice
to the rhythm of the other.</i>

1275
01:04:45.158 --> 01:04:46.250
Throbbing.

1276
01:04:46.954 --> 01:04:47.958
in my lips.

1277
01:04:48.392 --> 01:04:49.458
fingers.

1278
01:04:50.458 --> 01:04:52.291
and flesh of my temple.

1279
01:04:54.333 --> 01:04:55.224
Above all.

1280
01:04:56.220 --> 01:04:57.416
in my veins.

1281
01:04:58.292 --> 01:05:00.875
<i>Drum. and then the other drum.</i>

1282
01:05:11.135 --> 01:05:12.417
<i>I opened my eyes.</i>

1283
01:05:14.542 --> 01:05:16.834
<i>And it was then that I realized.</i>

1284
01:05:18.248 --> 01:05:20.042
<i>the drum was my heart.</i>

1285
01:05:22.125 --> 01:05:23.294
<i>and the other drum</i>

1286
01:05:24.067 --> 01:05:25.375
<i>had been his.</i>

1287
01:05:28.609 --> 01:05:31.042
<i>I saw him sitting
a length away from me.</i>

1288
01:05:32.879 --> 01:05:33.916
<i>Radiant.</i>

1289
01:05:35.292 --> 01:05:37.625
<i>And we sat there
for some time.</i>

1290
01:05:39.950 --> 01:05:43.617
<i>In throes
of increasing wonder...</i>

1291
01:05:49.833 --> 01:05:50.666
The end.

1292
01:05:53.450 --> 01:05:54.833
The beginning.

